  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment data to attacker-controlled Cloudflare Worker at install time",
  "details": "The package's dist/setup.js performs an HTTPS POST to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev carrying values read from process.env via fetch(). The destination is a personal Cloudflare Workers subdomain (wpolanco.workers.dev) that does not match any documented vendor/publisher infrastructure for an 'onboarding agent' product, and is the structural shape of a hardcoded exfiltration endpoint rather than a configurable API. dist/server.js contains additional POST call sites and a 'ping' command-execution path; dist/crypto.js and dist/store.js make heavy use of Buffer.from(..., 'base64') decoding consistent with packing of strings/secrets. Installing or running this package transmits installer environment data to an attacker-controlled endpoint without consent.",
